


                                    Angular - Front End Technology


                                        Basic Commands


                1. To create project - ng new projectName / ng new projectName --routing

                2. To run Angular project - ng serve / ng serve --open

                3. To generate component - ng g c componentName

                4. To generate service - ng g s serviceName




                                        Building Blocks


                1. Module - To import libraries (root Module - AppModule)

                2. Component - To create view {html,css,ts} - (root Component - AppComponent)

                3. Data Binding - share data inside a component

                    3.1 One way Binding - Data sharing only in one direction at a time

                        3.1.1 Component (ts) to View (html)

                            3.1.1.1 String Interpolation - {{expression}} 

                            3.1.1.2 Property Binding - [attribute name]="Property name"

                        3.1.2 View (html) to Component (ts)

                            3.1.2.1 Event Binding - (event-name)="function name()"

                            3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event - (event-name)="function name($event)"

                            3.1.2.3 Using Template referencing variable - #variable-name

                    3.2 Two way Binding - Data sharing in both direction at the same time

                            3.2.1 ngModel - import FormsModule in AppModule - [(ngModel)]="variable-name"


                4. Angular Routing - to set path for component in appRoutingModule
                    - use router-outlet selector in root component

                5. Dependency Injection

                6. Angular services

                7. ngSubmit 

                8. Angular Directives -  To manipulate DOM 

                    8.1 Component Directives

                    8.2 Structural Directives - prefix by *

                        8.2.1 *ngFor

